abstract: DES MOINES, Iowa, June 15.--The Democratic State Committee to-night called the State Convention to meet here on Thursday. Sept. 1. Fusion was only incidentally discussed, and an anti-monopoly campaign rather than anti-prohibition was foreshadowed by the discussion. The Greenback State Committee will meet next Friday to call its convention, after which the question of fusion will be on the carpet. Ex-Congressman Fredericks joint nomination seems now to be assured.

abstract: JACKSONVILLE, Fla., June 25.--Fire broke out last night and destroyed the brick block, corner of Bay and Clay streets, occupied by Clark  Loftus, furniture; Watson  Co., drugs, and Sable Brothers, leather.
